      • testStressSequence

        public void testStressSequence()
                        throws IOException
        Run a large #of pack/unpack operations on a sequence of long values to demonstrate correctness in that sequence. The sequence is the long values from -1 to 1M by one (dense coverage).
        Throws:
        IOException

      • testStressRandom

        public void testStressRandom()
                      throws IOException
        Run a large #of random pack/unpack operations to sample the space while showing correctness on those samples. The amount of compression due to packing for this test is very small since all bits are equally likely to be non-zero, so the #of bytes required on average to pack a long value is 8.
        Throws:
        IOException
